11:58.450 --> 11:59.749
She bought a condo

11:59.751 --> 12:01.951
and paid for Bridget's gastric bypass.

12:01.953 --> 12:03.887
Hmm.

12:03.889 --> 12:05.088
Josh, honey,

12:05.090 --> 12:06.322
I feel for you.

12:06.324 --> 12:08.424
Coming home can't be easy.

12:08.426 --> 12:10.226
You have lots of messes to clean up.

12:10.228 --> 12:12.162
I mean, I guess so.

12:12.164 --> 12:14.430
It's a shame. I miss Rebecca.

12:15.183 --> 12:17.933
I made a place in my
heart for another daughter.

12:18.487 --> 12:20.970
Did you two smooth things over?

12:20.972 --> 12:23.683
She was so in love with you.

12:23.708 --> 12:26.453
She must be so disappointed, right?

12:26.478 --> 12:28.578
She's a-a bit disappointed.

12:28.580 --> 12:31.214
- Um, she left a few.. couple messages.
- Oh.

12:31.216 --> 12:33.383
But, um, I think we should, um,

12:33.385 --> 12:35.652
just give each other a
little space right now.

12:36.513 --> 12:39.088
Anyways, I don't really
want to talk about it.

12:39.090 --> 12:40.523
I just want to move on.

12:40.525 --> 12:42.158
That's very wise.

12:42.160 --> 12:43.443
Mm-hmm.

12:43.468 --> 12:45.835
No, I got to start making
some more mature decisions.

12:46.064 --> 12:47.771
Taking myself seriously.

12:48.037 --> 12:49.866
This morning, I called Alex,

12:49.868 --> 12:51.301
asked him for my job back,

12:51.576 --> 12:54.475
he said okay, and when I get there,

12:54.706 --> 12:56.673
I'm gonna ask for that raise I deserve.

12:56.675 --> 12:59.676
Disappear and ask for a raise.

12:59.678 --> 13:02.011
- Seems like a good plan.
- Thanks, Dad.

13:02.441 --> 13:03.980
I want to focus on my future right now.

13:03.982 --> 13:05.949
All the good things ahead of me.

13:05.951 --> 13:09.052
Oh, my God, what was that?

13:09.054 --> 13:10.320
Joseph!

13:10.322 --> 13:12.689
I've been telling you to
get that jacaranda trimmed.

13:12.691 --> 13:14.417
Slapping the window again.

13:15.093 --> 13:17.206
Oh, God, I-I thought that was...

13:18.630 --> 13:21.064
that was like out of a
scary movie or something.

13:26.948 --> 13:29.439
That's right. Laugh it off, Channy Boy.

13:29.441 --> 13:30.707
I'm coming for you.

13:30.709 --> 13:32.475
You know, Rebecca better watch out

13:32.477 --> 13:34.143
how she talks to me,
because I don't even care,

13:34.145 --> 13:36.446
I will take out these hoop
earrings and yank a pony.

13:36.997 --> 13:38.781
Oh, come on, you can't take
what she said personally.

13:38.783 --> 13:39.983
She's not in her right mind.

13:39.985 --> 13:42.218
Which is exactly why I'm here.

13:42.220 --> 13:43.620
She's so lucky she cray.

13:43.645 --> 13:45.955
Oh, come on. I am so frustrated.

13:45.957 --> 13:47.991
I mean, I tried to
track her, but, you know,

13:47.993 --> 13:49.826
she turned off the location
services on her phone,

13:49.828 --> 13:51.861
and she doesn't have her
car that I put the GPS on,

13:51.863 --> 13:54.297
and the tracker I put in her shoulder

13:54.299 --> 13:56.799
- ran out of batteries months ago.
- What?

13:57.357 --> 13:58.801
Oh, it's just a little "boop."

13:58.803 --> 14:00.603
They don't even feel it. You have one.

14:00.605 --> 14:01.938
But don't worry,

14:01.940 --> 14:03.339
- it's dead, too.
- Wait, what?

14:04.537 --> 14:06.009
Oh, my God.

14:06.011 --> 14:07.373
Yeah.

14:08.576 --> 14:09.756
I-I'm sorry.

14:10.170 --> 14:13.228
Look, when we became friends,
I-I meant to tell you.

14:14.735 --> 14:16.753
Before you and Josh broke
up, Rebecca and I were on

14:16.755 --> 14:19.689
a full-on sabotage mission.

14:20.079 --> 14:22.125
I tracked you, I hacked your stuff,

14:22.127 --> 14:23.693
I may have blackmailed

14:23.718 --> 14:25.859
some people in your
life for information,

14:25.884 --> 14:28.031
but I am not proud of it.

14:28.033 --> 14:29.933
- Paula!
- I know, I know.

14:29.935 --> 14:33.102
But I just wanted Rebecca's
love story to... to work out.

14:33.838 --> 14:35.163
I'm sorry.

14:35.941 --> 14:37.573
Do you forgive me?

14:37.575 --> 14:38.608
God, this sucks.

14:38.610 --> 14:41.344
I mean... I thought you
guys were my friends,

14:41.346 --> 14:43.680
and you were manipulating
me the whole time.

14:43.682 --> 14:46.950
We were manipulating
you, but then we were-n't.

14:48.386 --> 14:51.521
Okay, look, I am just
as surprised as you are

14:51.523 --> 14:52.956
that you and I are friends.

14:52.958 --> 14:56.926
I mean, you are literally... the
girl I hated in high school.

14:56.928 --> 14:58.531
But I am your friend now,

14:58.556 --> 15:00.563
and... I love you,

15:00.565 --> 15:02.932
and Rebecca is your
friend and she loves you,

15:02.934 --> 15:05.969
and female friendships are very strange,

15:05.971 --> 15:08.204
and I just... stop complaining.

15:08.206 --> 15:09.539
Because we have to help Rebecca now,

15:09.541 --> 15:12.475
even if you think she
deserves a yank on the pony.

15:13.486 --> 15:15.956
Now let's go.

15:52.885 --> 15:54.885
Hello? Who is this?

15:58.832 --> 16:00.865
How did you get this number?

16:01.116 --> 16:03.745
This is a private line. I
got it on my 13th birth...

17:09.806 --> 17:11.416
Rebecca

17:11.449 --> 17:13.449
Rebecca!

17:13.887 --> 17:16.223
- Rebecca?
- Rebecca

17:16.248 --> 17:18.661
Hey *** Thanks so much
for coming out, you guys.

17:18.685 --> 17:20.590
because this has been a hard night

17:20.637 --> 17:22.928
Yeah, this whole thing totally sounds
like an intervention

17:22.976 --> 17:24.976
I went to five of those for my uncle.

17:24.978 --> 17:26.411
Last one was actually an intervention

17:26.413 --> 17:29.021
because he couldn't stop
watching Intervention on A&E.

17:29.716 --> 17:31.443
I mean, it worked, but then
he moved on to Hoarders.

17:31.466 --> 17:33.966
Now he's got, like,
80 of those on his DVR.

17:33.968 --> 17:36.202
And, you guessed it,
he will not delete them.

17:36.204 --> 17:38.004
They're just piling up.

17:38.376 --> 17:40.573
You know what? Just realized I'm
gonna have to intervene again.

17:40.575 --> 17:41.574
Wow.

17:41.576 --> 17:43.342
I have crazy relatives, but all we do

17:43.344 --> 17:46.235
is talk about them when they
leave, like a normal family.

17:46.260 --> 17:48.414
It was a really tough conversation.

17:48.416 --> 17:51.083
Rebecca was obviously very upset.

17:51.085 --> 17:54.086
She started saying crazy things.

17:54.088 --> 17:56.189
Like, out of the blue, she was like,

17:56.191 --> 17:58.791
"Oh, White Josh does not
want to have a baby with you,"

17:58.793 --> 18:00.960
which is crazy because

18:00.962 --> 18:03.062
well, one: how would she know that?

18:03.064 --> 18:05.860
And two: you said you
would consider it, right?

18:05.885 --> 18:07.633
So she's way off.

18:08.375 --> 18:10.169
You said you would consider it, right?

18:10.171 --> 18:11.771
- Yeah-huh.
- Yep.

18:14.995 --> 18:16.443
Yeah, uh, I think I
see Heather up there.

18:16.468 --> 18:17.777
Might just run up,
see how she's doing.

18:17.779 --> 18:20.079
No, no, no. No, no, no,
Hector, you got to stay.

18:20.081 --> 18:22.048
Ain't no search party
like a Hector search party.

18:22.050 --> 18:23.783
You're great at this. In high school,

18:23.785 --> 18:25.451
you found that girl who
drank all that Sambuca

18:25.453 --> 18:27.119
and passed out in her
neighbor's yard, remember?

18:27.121 --> 18:28.521
Oh, yeah, Susie Reynolds.

18:28.523 --> 18:29.956
You know she's a state senator now?

18:29.958 --> 18:31.224
No way, I thought she was an escort.

18:31.226 --> 18:32.792
No, that's Angie Washburn. Oh, right.

18:32.794 --> 18:35.228
Joshua, if you're not
really considering the baby

18:35.230 --> 18:36.395
and you're just humoring me...

18:36.397 --> 18:38.030
Oh, boy. Darryl...

18:38.032 --> 18:39.860
I'm out. Heather, wait up.

18:41.236 --> 18:42.869
Yeah...

18:44.271 --> 18:45.670
I can't get over this.

18:45.695 --> 18:47.962
I had no idea this was in her past.

18:48.042 --> 18:49.141
It's a big blow.

18:49.143 --> 18:50.643
I guess I'm partly to blame,

18:50.645 --> 18:53.446
'cause I'm the one who told
you to go for it with her.

18:53.448 --> 18:55.258
I got too involved
in your personal life.

18:55.283 --> 18:56.749
I regret it.

18:56.751 --> 18:58.417
Now can we go back to the restaurant?

18:58.419 --> 19:00.686
Because we are waiting for a lava cake.

19:00.688 --> 19:02.855
Yeah, they said it
would take 20 minutes,

19:02.857 --> 19:05.024
and we've been here for 30, so...

19:05.026 --> 19:06.425
You know what? I'm sorry.

19:06.427 --> 19:07.956
I feel terrible.

19:08.329 --> 19:10.763
I interrupted your date,
which you're paying for

19:10.765 --> 19:12.932
with the money I give you every week!

19:12.934 --> 19:13.966
You're right. Let's stay.

19:13.968 --> 19:15.268
I don't even really want lava cake.

19:15.722 --> 19:17.236
I do.

19:17.238 --> 19:18.871
I do, too.

19:23.144 --> 19:25.278
- Oh, hey.
- Hey. Hi.

19:26.074 --> 19:27.280
Glad I saw you.

19:27.282 --> 19:30.983
I had to get away from
White Josh and Darryl. Man...

19:30.985 --> 19:33.019
Ugh. Well, you can walk with me.

19:33.021 --> 19:34.654
I'm not actually looking for Rebecca,

19:34.656 --> 19:36.789
because you can't fix people
who don't want to be helped,

19:36.791 --> 19:37.857
- but...
- Hmm.

19:37.859 --> 19:39.692
... swinging a flashlight around is fun.

19:39.694 --> 19:40.760
So Velma.

19:40.762 --> 19:41.961
I'm totally a Shaggy.

19:41.963 --> 19:44.730
Oh, my God, you totally are, so...

19:47.268 --> 19:50.303
Oh. I'm sorry.

19:50.305 --> 19:51.504
No, I liked it.

19:51.881 --> 19:53.940
Your arms are really
smooth. Do you depilate?

19:54.342 --> 19:55.641
I do not.

19:55.643 --> 19:57.743
Just naturally silky.

19:57.745 --> 19:59.245
Good for surfing.

19:59.247 --> 20:01.581
I do shave the hair around my nipples.

20:01.583 --> 20:02.815
I mean, who doesn't?

20:04.852 --> 20:07.386
Okay, that actually kind
of freaked me out, so...

20:07.388 --> 20:08.910
hold me, Silky Arms.

20:55.197 --> 20:56.896
Rebecca!

20:57.833 --> 20:58.865
Rebecca!

20:58.867 --> 21:01.334
I know this is you! Stop it!

21:01.336 --> 21:02.702
Leave me alone!

21:02.930 --> 21:05.592
I'm not gonna let you
get to me, you hear me?

21:06.780 --> 21:08.679
I'm not afraid of you.

21:16.251 --> 21:17.917
So I'm totally getting to him,

21:17.919 --> 21:20.754
and he's totally afraid
of me... It's great!

21:21.139 --> 21:23.423
Jarl. Hey, hey, hey.

21:23.425 --> 21:25.786
Wake up, Jarlsberg. I'm trying
to tell you something important.

21:25.811 --> 21:27.644
I am tired.

21:27.646 --> 21:30.047
You woke me up in the
middle of the night.

21:30.049 --> 21:32.482
I have to get up early
to go to the Autry Museum

21:32.484 --> 21:34.006
of the American West.

21:34.031 --> 21:35.798
Ew. What? Don't go there.
It's just a bunch of pictures

21:35.823 --> 21:36.989
of Roy Rogers.

21:37.223 --> 21:38.822
You mean Gene Autry?

21:38.824 --> 21:40.457
Who cares? Anyway, Jarl.

21:40.459 --> 21:41.625
You won't believe what's happening.

21:41.627 --> 21:43.393
So I have decided to reenact

21:43.395 --> 21:45.329
every great revenge movie ever made,

21:45.331 --> 21:48.265
and it's... ugh! It is so
good to see Josh squirm.

21:48.267 --> 21:51.356
But what happens after you do
all these scary things to him?

21:51.381 --> 21:52.703
I-I don't know.

21:52.705 --> 21:53.981
I-I feel better, I guess?

21:54.006 --> 21:56.077
No. You die.

21:56.102 --> 21:58.327
Whoa, what?

21:58.383 --> 22:00.750
That's how every one
of these movies ends.

22:00.752 --> 22:03.052
Stabbing, shooting, drowning.

22:03.054 --> 22:04.821
The monster has to be killed.

22:04.823 --> 22:08.024
Once you start this,
skagget I postkassen.

22:08.026 --> 22:09.192
Huh?

22:09.194 --> 22:11.874
You have a beard in your mailbox.

22:11.906 --> 22:13.539
That doesn't clarify anything.

22:13.541 --> 22:15.775
It means you are about to be caught.

22:15.777 --> 22:18.511
And when you are caught, you are killed.

22:21.349 --> 22:22.882
No.

22:22.884 --> 22:24.450
No. That-that's...

22:24.452 --> 22:27.854
No. That's-that's not
how my movie has to end.

22:27.856 --> 22:29.922
No. Uh-uh. No, no. No.

22:30.314 --> 22:33.826
I am independently
financed... in my own mind.

22:33.828 --> 22:36.128
Jarl, don't you see? This
story is not just about

22:36.130 --> 22:37.663
blind evil revenge,

22:37.665 --> 22:39.906
this is, this is about retribution.

22:39.931 --> 22:41.831
And redistribution of misery.

22:41.833 --> 22:44.968
Making Josh feel like
I've felt my whole life.

22:44.970 --> 22:48.071
Wait, you were unhappy
before you met him?

22:48.073 --> 22:50.206
Then how is this his fault?

22:50.208 --> 22:52.375
What? He exploited that unhappiness!

22:52.377 --> 22:54.944
He-he took his normal
and rubbed it in my face.

22:54.946 --> 23:00.250
So what I am hearing is, it's
not really about Josh, per Se.

23:00.252 --> 23:03.786
Josh is more a symbol
of effortless normalcy

23:03.788 --> 23:06.389
from which you always felt excluded.

23:09.461 --> 23:10.627
No, it's about Josh.

23:10.629 --> 23:12.195
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

23:12.197 --> 23:13.963
You're not making any sense.

23:13.965 --> 23:15.431
Although your English
is fantastic, so I mean,

23:15.433 --> 23:17.000
bravo, Danish school system.

23:24.042 --> 23:26.142
So, we crapped out.

23:26.144 --> 23:27.410
We can't find her.

23:27.412 --> 23:29.045
Now what do we do?

23:29.047 --> 23:30.380
Guys, I'm telling you.

23:30.382 --> 23:32.415
She's either gonna
come back or she's not.

23:32.417 --> 23:34.083
We just have to face that.

23:34.085 --> 23:35.552
I mean, she probably just took an Uber

23:35.554 --> 23:36.853
to the outlets or something.

23:36.855 --> 23:39.189
That's where I would go if
I turned on all my friends.

23:39.214 --> 23:42.659
- I'm a real outlet girl.
- I feel so terrible. I mean, I failed

23:42.661 --> 23:44.494
as a best friend and matron of honor.

23:44.789 --> 23:46.849
And a parent, I guess.

23:50.005 --> 23:51.968
Wait, do you guys agree with Rebecca?

23:51.970 --> 23:54.204
Do you think I'm a bad mom?

23:54.206 --> 23:55.538
Uh...

23:55.540 --> 23:58.441
Oh, two-part harmony bad?

23:58.443 --> 24:00.143
- Really?
- Truth?

24:00.145 --> 24:01.945
You're not the most attentive parent.

24:02.592 --> 24:03.947
Brendan's my weed guy.

24:03.949 --> 24:06.701
He's starting a business? That's great!

24:07.385 --> 24:08.985
What? Not the right response?

24:08.987 --> 24:10.253
Hey, can you guys keep it down?

24:10.255 --> 24:12.488
Penny and George are asleep.

24:12.490 --> 24:13.617
They're so beat.

24:13.642 --> 24:15.091
Who? What?

24:15.093 --> 24:16.793
Why are you in my house?

24:16.795 --> 24:19.195
Rebecca could come back
here. I have to wait for her.

24:19.197 --> 24:20.230
I called the police, but apparently

24:20.232 --> 24:21.297
we can't report her missing

24:21.299 --> 24:22.765
for another 36 hours,

24:22.767 --> 24:25.235
because she's just a person
who walked out of her own house.

24:26.404 --> 24:28.171
Anyway, shh.

24:28.173 --> 24:29.802
- Right.
- Okay.

24:29.827 --> 24:31.975
Well, I guess I'll just
keep trying to call her,

24:31.977 --> 24:33.910
and check the tracker,
in case she slips up.

24:33.912 --> 24:36.112
Speaking of which, I am
gonna go see the doctor,

24:36.114 --> 24:37.847
get this tracker out of my shoulder.

24:37.849 --> 24:39.515
- What?
- Suit yourself,

24:39.517 --> 24:41.517
but I just think you
should get a new battery,

24:41.519 --> 24:42.952
'cause if you get human trafficked,

24:42.954 --> 24:44.187
you'll be glad you have it.

24:44.189 --> 24:46.389
Cool, cool. That all sounds terrifying.

24:46.391 --> 24:48.458
Anyways, I'm gonna go
get breakfast with Hector

24:48.460 --> 24:51.594
to distract myself from the
fact that Rebecca was right.

24:51.841 --> 24:55.231
I am an aimless cynic who
has no plans for my future.

24:55.233 --> 24:58.334
Um, and I do have to
do something about that

24:58.336 --> 25:01.371
at some point, in my
life, like, for sure.

25:01.373 --> 25:02.405
But right now, I'm just

25:02.407 --> 25:03.439
gonna go get breakfast burritos

25:03.441 --> 25:05.740
with Hector and his sweet, sweet ass.

25:07.092 --> 25:08.077
Okay, bye.

25:08.079 --> 25:09.802
Okay. Bye.

25:11.967 --> 25:14.417
Thank you so much for
giving me my job back.

25:14.419 --> 25:16.986
You know, while I was
up in priest school...

25:16.988 --> 25:19.022
- Preschool?
- Priest school.

25:19.024 --> 25:21.024
Oh. That makes sense.

25:21.026 --> 25:23.192
So, I've really been
thinking a lot lately,

25:23.194 --> 25:25.862
and... I'm worth a lot more than...

25:25.864 --> 25:27.230
Bro, I got to stop you.

25:27.232 --> 25:28.998
First, I think you're
about to ask for a raise

25:29.000 --> 25:31.234
after I graciously
gave you your job back,

25:31.236 --> 25:33.403
so way to go on the cojones.

25:33.772 --> 25:35.975
But, dude, I've got a problem.

25:36.000 --> 25:38.162
I got an anonymous tip about you.

25:38.410 --> 25:40.376
Aw. I didn't know there was a tip jar

25:40.378 --> 25:42.679
for the back office assistant managers.

25:42.681 --> 25:44.414
People are so thoughtful.

25:44.416 --> 25:47.690
No. Someone called with
some information about you.

25:48.034 --> 25:51.596
You want to explain why I
found all this in your locker?

25:56.667 --> 25:59.062
Alex, come on. I-I didn't do that.

25:59.558 --> 26:01.164
Dude, I don't steal.

26:01.783 --> 26:04.417
Wait, anonymous information tip?

26:05.940 --> 26:07.737
Bro, I-I know who it is.

26:07.739 --> 26:09.238
I-I know who called you.

26:09.565 --> 26:11.974
Rebecca. S-She's coming after me

26:11.976 --> 26:13.376
really hard right now.

26:13.378 --> 26:15.078
She-she planted all
that stuff in there.

26:15.080 --> 26:16.484
Maybe.

26:17.082 --> 26:18.281
I believe you.

26:18.283 --> 26:19.781
I don't know.

26:19.806 --> 26:21.284
I still have to suspend you.

26:21.286 --> 26:23.653
- Wait, what? No...
- Yeah. Sorry.

26:23.655 --> 26:25.221
Corporate is uptight.

26:25.223 --> 26:27.156
They don't like stealing. It's weird.

26:27.158 --> 26:28.421
Sorry, bro.

26:28.793 --> 26:30.765
Pack your flip-flops and go.

26:35.342 --> 26:38.186
Oh, this is where I left my flip-flops.

26:38.670 --> 26:40.850
Well, that's an upside.

26:54.545 --> 26:55.685
Hi, Josh.

26:55.687 --> 26:56.786
Where's your mom?

26:56.788 --> 26:58.154
You might want to check.

26:58.156 --> 26:59.856
Hope Lourdes is okay.

26:59.858 --> 27:01.057
Lourdes, it's so wonderful

27:01.059 --> 27:02.892
that we get to spend some time together.

27:02.894 --> 27:03.960
I know!

27:03.962 --> 27:06.295
- Shall we?
- My pleasure.

27:06.297 --> 27:08.631
I think this will be a day
that you'll never forget.

27:19.356 --> 27:23.253
I used to come here every
year with Josh and the girls.

27:23.278 --> 27:25.612
They grew up and lost
interest in carnivals,

27:25.614 --> 27:27.121
